        "release_notes": {
            "en-US": "* Do not attempt blockquote reordering when composing a plaintext message with no blockquotes.\n* Fix the code reading identity-specific prefs.\n* The easiest way to do this requires Thunderbird 7+. Will add support for older versions if anyone complains.\n* Remove innerHTML from everything but the heading catcher."
        },
        "reviewed": null,
        "url": "https://addons.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/addon/posting-style-enforcer/versions/1.4",
        "version": "1.4"
    },
    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "If all goes well, you will never again have to know that an email was not formatted to your liking. When viewing or quoting a message, this rearranges the HTML so that bottom-posting or top-posting is enforced. This may be a nasty surprise to the person at the other end!\n\n* Supports moving \"Foo wrote:\" headings.\n* Attempts to remove quoted signatures.\n* Changes \"&gt;\" symbols and gmail blockquotes to mozilla blockquotes.\n* Allows blacklisting and whitelisting certain contacts.\n* Does not work for Hotmail."
    },
